          "date": "2015-09-11 10:05:22.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "subject": "LU-7139 test: Fixing file size calculation test_78 in sanity",
        "message": "LU-7139 test: Fixing file size calculation test_78 in sanity\n\nWhen using opaque calculation of file size, the test used to fail in\nlack of disk space, more robust file size calculation should be used.\nSo using probing technique for calculating the file size.\nFirst write operation is done using dd and file size equal to\nreturned bytes by dd is set to do direct I/O. It makes more\nsense because direct I/O is well defined for overwrite case.\n\nChange-Id: Id2cf42d9ba2688ea5c8f3bbd7cdd53e1a8ddd940\nSeagate-bug-id: MRP-1166\nSigned-off-by: Ashish Maurya <ashish.maurya@seagate.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
